INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (1,'8 Best Zapier Alternatives (With Pros, Cons & Quick Verdic','8-best-zapier-alternatives-with-pros-cons--quick-verdic','<h2>Manage the Root page</h2><p>Every Extranet site is built on a hierarchy that begins at the Root page. Before you can add pages to your site, you must first prepare the Root page.</p><p>The security model for your extranet is directly related to the hierarchy of the site. As you populate your site, each page you create inherits the security settings from the page above it in the hierarchy. Therefore, in order to build an effective access strategy, the top page should have the least restrictions on security. As you add pages, you can restrict access to a smaller set of people at each level in the hierarchy. For more information on this topic, see <a href=\"https://eprostarchive.med.miami.edu/Common/_Eprost/help/Admin/PEAplan_your_security_policy.htm\">Plan your page security model</a>.</p><p>Users can see a representation of your hierarchy each time they use the breadcrumb navigator in the site:</p><p><img src=\"https://eprostarchive.med.miami.edu/Common/_Eprost/help/Admin/Breadcrumb.gif\" alt=\"Breadcrumb.gif\"></p><p><strong>To manage Root</strong></p><p>Log onto your site as an administrator.</p><p>In the breadcrumb navigator, click <strong>Root</strong>.</p><p>In the top-right corner of the page, click <strong>Properties</strong>.</p><p>Add or change items on the Page Properties form. You can, for example, write a description or include an image.</p><p>When you\'re done, click <strong>OK</strong>.</p><p>In the top-right corner of the page, click <strong>Permissions</strong> to set permissions on the root page.</p><p>For detailed instructions on this task, see <a href=\"https://eprostarchive.med.miami.edu/Common/_Eprost/help/Admin/pe_restrict_access.htm\">Set permissions on pages, components, and resources</a>.</p><p>When you are through making changes, click <strong>OK</strong>.</p><p><strong>Important</strong></p><p>Owners for Root — Most, if not all, sites limit ownership of the Root page to users who have the user role of Site Manager. This user role is almost always given to a very select number of users, including the system administrator. For security purposes, it is important to limit ownership to very few and trusted users.</p>',NULL,'2022-08-12 07:04:56','2022-08-12 10:27:43'),(2,'10 Best Managed WordPress Hosting Providers for High Traffic Sites','10-best-managed-wordpress-hosting-providers-for-high-traffic-sites','<p>Looking for the best managed WordPress hosting providers in 2022?</p><p>Managed WordPress web hosting saves your time and offers better security and speed.</p><p>Managed web hosting simply means the web hosting provider will take care of the technical part like installing WordPress core updates, setting up automatic backups, offering free speed optimization, etc.</p><p>While WordPress has made it easier for people to manage their websites, some people are still confused when it comes to making a hosting choice. This is why many individuals that have been planning to <a href=\"https://bloggerspassion.com/how-to-start-a-blog/\">launch a self-hosted WordPress site</a> are still stuck today.</p><p>Because we don’t want you to make a bad decision when choosing a web host, we’ve made a detailed list of the best managed WordPress hosts for 2022.</p><p>These best managed hosting providers will ensure your website’s security, <a href=\"https://bloggerspassion.com/speed-up-wordpress/\">faster loading times,</a> and swift performance so you can focus on promoting and growing your website.</p><p><strong>Our Recommendation</strong></p><p><strong>Our #1 Choice</strong><picture><source srcset=\"https://bloggerspassion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/wpxhosting-logo.webp\" type=\"image/webp\"><source srcset=\"https://bloggerspassion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/wpxhosting-logo.png\" type=\"image/png\"><img src=\"https://bloggerspassion.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/1